First time run:

1. Get .env directory from developer

2. Contact developer to get IP address whitelisted with DB

3. Create virtual enviornment
    python3 -m venv env

4. Activate virtual environment
    source env/bin/activate

5. Install requirements
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    
6. Run application locally
    flask run --port 5100 --debug

7. Follow link in previous commands output to access application


References:

https://dev.to/cre8stevedev/building-a-full-stack-web-application-using-flask-python-web-framework-part-two-1fc3